stylometry: Data mining is searching through a large set of data to find similarities, patterns or other like natures of the data. The clusters method is an example of data mining. By using the clusters method, we grouped data into subsets. We then took the average of the data and divided that by the standard deviation to get the standardize set of data. After that we used the sumxmy2 function, index function and match function. Once all the numbers were calculated and all the data was put into their corresponding subset, a sensitivity analysis was performed to make the correct subsets. All the information was grouped to a certain subset. Business use this information to predict patterns or behaviors that allows them to make proactive business decisions.
